# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Overview
React application built with Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework:** React 19
- **Build Tool:** Vite
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **Package Manager:** pnpm

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── components/     # Reusable UI components
│   └── ui/         # shadcn/ui components
├── pages/          # Page components
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks
├── lib/            # Utility functions
├── types/          # TypeScript types
└── main.tsx        # Application entry point
```

## Commands
- `pnpm dev` - Start development server
- `pnpm build` - Build for production
- `pnpm preview` - Preview production build
- `pnpm lint` - Run ESLint
- `pnpm test` - Run tests

## Development Notes
- Components follow atomic design principles
- Use shadcn/ui for consistent UI components
- State management via React hooks (useState, useContext)
- API calls should use custom hooks in hooks/
